```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Form</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Simple Form</h1>
    <form id="simple-form">
        <!-- Label for the Name field -->
        <label for="name">Name:</label>
        <!-- Input field for the Name -->
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>

        <!-- Label for the Email field -->
        <label for="email">Email:</label>
        <!-- Input field for the Email -->
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>

        <!-- Label for the Message field -->
        <label for="message">Message:</label>
        <!-- Textarea for the Message -->
        <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" required></textarea>

        <!-- Submit button -->
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    <!-- Div to display the result -->
    <div id="result"></div>

    <script>
        // Function to handle form submission
        function handleSubmit(event) {
            // Prevent the default form submission behavior
            // This prevents the form from submitting via the traditional method
            event.preventDefault();

            // Get form data
            // Retrieve the value of the Name input field
            const name = document.getElementById('name').value;
            // Retrieve the value of the Email input field
            const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
            // Retrieve the value of the Message textarea
            const message = document.getElementById('message').value;

            // Validate form data
            // Check if all required fields are filled
            if (!name || !email || !message) {
                // If any field is empty, show an alert
                alert('Please fill in all fields.');
                // Return early to stop further execution
                return;
            }

            // Simulate storing data in localStorage
            // Convert the form data to a JSON string
            const formData = JSON.stringify({
                name: name,
                email: email,
                message: message
            });

            // Store the JSON string in localStorage
            localStorage.setItem('formData', formData);

            // Display success message
            // Update the #result div to show a success message
            document.getElementById('result').innerText = 'Form submitted successfully!';
        }

        // Add event listener to the form
        // Attach the handleSubmit function to the form's submit event
        document.getElementById('simple-form').addEventListener('submit', handleSubmit);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Detailed Breakdown

1. **HTML Form Elements**:
   - **Labels and Inputs**:
     ```html
     <label for="name">Name:</label>
     <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>

     <label for="email">Email:</label>
     <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>

     <label for="message">Message:</label>
     <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" required></textarea>
     ```
     - **Labels**: These provide text descriptions for the form fields, enhancing accessibility.
     - **Inputs and Textarea**: These are the actual form fields where users can enter their data.
     - **Required Attribute**: Ensures that the fields must be filled out before the form can be submitted.

2. **JavaScript Functions**:
   - **handleSubmit Function**:
     ```javascript
     function handleSubmit(event) {
         // Prevent the default form submission behavior
         event.preventDefault();

         // Get form data
         const name = document.getElementById('name').value;
         const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
         const message = document.getElementById('message').value;

         // Validate form data
         if (!name || !email || !message) {
             alert('Please fill in all fields.');
             return;
         }

         // Simulate storing data in localStorage
         const formData = JSON.stringify({
             name: name,
             email: email,
             message: message
         });

         localStorage.setItem('formData', formData);

         // Display success message
         document.getElementById('result').innerText = 'Form submitted successfully!';
     }
     ```
     - **Prevent Default Behavior**: `event.preventDefault()` stops the form from submitting the traditional way, allowing us to handle it programmatically.
     - **Get Form Data**: `document.getElementById` retrieves the values from the form fields.
     - **Validation**: Checks if all required fields are filled. If not, shows an alert and returns early.
     - **Store Data**: Converts the form data to a JSON string and stores it in `localStorage` using `localStorage.setItem`.
     - **Success Message**: Updates the `#result` div to display a success message.

3. **Event Listener**:
   ```javascript
