   const bodyParser = require('body-parser');

   const app = express();
   const port = 3000;

   // Middleware to parse JSON bodies
   app.use(bodyParser.json());

   // Route to handle form submission
   app.post('/save-name', (req, res) => {
       const { name } = req.body;

       // Save the name to a file or database (for simplicity, we'll just log it here)
       console.log(`Received name: ${name}`);

       // Respond with a success message
       res.json({ message: 'Name saved successfully!' });
   });

   // Start the server
   app.listen(port, () => {
       console.log(`Server running on http://localhost:${port}`);
   });
   ```

### Running the Application

1. **Start the Node.js Server:**
   ```sh
   node server.js
   ```

2. **Open the HTML File in a Browser:**
   Open `index.html` in your browser. You should see a form where you can enter your name. When you submit the form, the data will be sent to the server using AJAX, and you will see a success message displayed on the page.

This example illustrates how modern web technologies build upon past innovations to create more robust, user-friendly, and efficient forms. The combination of HTML5 for better form validation, JavaScript for client-side interactivity, and Node.js for server-side processing demonstrates the evolution of web forms from simple inputs to sophisticated, dynamic tools.
